<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 15 at 6:22PM CDT  by NWS Amarillo</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of Armstrong, Randall,
southwestern Wheeler, eastern Oldham, Carson, eastern Deaf Smith,
Gray, Potter and Donley Counties through 730 PM CDT...
At 621 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong outflow boundary
as a result of previous thunderstorms, along a line extending from 6
miles northwest of Codman to 10 miles east of Channing. Movement was
southeast at 50 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Amarillo, Pampa, Canyon, Borger, Panhandle, Clarendon, Claude,
Fritch, White Deer, Lake Tanglewood, Mclean, Groom, Lefors,
Skellytown, Howardwick, Hedley, Buffalo Lake, Bushland, Lelia Lake
and Lake Mcclellan.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...55 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM CDT for the Panhandle
of Texas.</instruction>
